8:
We're dealing with a Gaean fleet,
Captain! We should surrendâ€”
14:
You're surrounded, Zelimir! Return
your plundered goods and
surrender!
15: If you value your life, do it now!
18:
Yarr-har-har! You sea dogs sure
love to bark.
21:
These goods be mine now. Just try
to prove me wrong!
24: ...Then may your greed sink with you!
38:
...You there, little one. Where might I
be?
41: Good morning. This is Paradise Isle.
45:
Heh... I wonder how long I was adrift
at sea.
47:
The name's Zelimir. Perhaps I be
owin' you a favor for saving me...
51:
...So you're saying that you were
transporting cargo when your ship
met with disaster in a storm?
55:
Aye... A terrible storm, she was. My
ship was destroyed, and not a piece
remains.
57:
Forgive me, but I'll be repayin' me
debt to ya after I recover from me
losses.
62:
You're full of holes. You want us to
believe you ran into a
naturally-occuring storm of musket
balls?
70:
Yarr-har-har! Don't tell me we be
sailin' in the same ship?
80:
Don't shoot! These two can hold
them off!
91:
It's time to make our escape. Follow
me.
98:
What's a pirate without a ship? We'll
be procurin' one of those, first...
106:
Arr-har-har! That's a fine expression,
lass.
112: It be time to set sail. All aboard.
120: Zelimir. We can't stay on this ship.
125:
Then what, prey tell, do you intend to
do instead?
134:
Sorry, matey. You're in league with a
filthy bilge rat, now.
137:
Make up yer minds. If you value your
lives, come with meâ€”
148: What might you be on about, lass?
154:
I'll be askin' you a second time, lass.
Where might I be?
157:
This is Starview Village. We can see
many worlds from here.
161:
Arrr... Worlds, you say? Those things
in the sky...
172:
You need rest. Unless you desire a
violent revival, just lay still for a while.
176:
Amazing. With a good enough
doctor, even a foolhardy dog like me
can keep on breathing...
181:
...You're enjoying this, aren't you?
"Pirate Captain Zelimir."
184:
The two who treated your wounds
explained to me that you were a
terrible villain of the seas.
188:
Suppose I am. Do you be aimin' to
make a deal with the Gaean
Government?
191:
We won't do anything. That girl's
already accepted you, after all.
194:
However, you mustn't attempt any
foolishness here. You'll find that the
local residents are far more
fearsome than the pirates you know.
197:
...Now you're the one who be enjoyin'
this.
201:
...Perhaps you're right. Some might
even say I've changed in my time
here.
203:
...And even a terrible villain can
return to the light in a place like this.
208:
Return to the light? Hah... That be
some lousy wording...
211:
I'll steal everything back... No matter
how many times it takes...
213: I be Zelimir the pirate, after all...
